text.tspan: Maternal mortality is the share of women who die from pregnancy-related causes while pregnant or within 42 days
of pregnancy termination. Neonatal mortality is the share of newborns who die within the first 28 days of life.
Data source: World Health Organization (via World Bank), UN Inter-agency Group for Child Mortality Estimation (via World Bank)
